.TH "ssh-x-agent" "1" "" "Version Latest" "SSH-X Agent Utilities"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
\f[V]ssh-x-agent\f[R] - A cli of SSH Agent Utilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
ssh-x-agent command options
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
where \f[V]command\f[R] can be:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]init\f[R] - Start one agent by computer (not one by session) and
return env statement.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]kill\f[R] - Stop the agent process (given by
\f[V]SSH_AGENT_PID\f[R] or any ssh-agent process).
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]state\f[R] - State of the agent
.SH SECURITY NOTE AND LIFETIME
.PP
\f[V]ssh-agent\f[R] enhances security by allowing you to use
passphrase-protected SSH keys without entering the passphrase every
time.
.PP
However, anyone with access to the agent\[cq]s socket SSH_AUTH_SOCK and
your user permissions can use the keys managed by the agent.
.PP
That\[cq]s why by default, we set a lifetime of 15m (3 times the default
of 5m for sudo).
.PP
You can override it with the SSH_X_LIFE environment
.PP
Example:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
# disable
export SSH_X_LIFE=0
# 1h
export SSH_X_LIFE=1h
\f[R]
.fi
